svg.title: Artboard 23
svg.text: The swallow may fly south with the sun,
seek warmer hot lands in winter, yet these are not strangers to our land.
Not at all. They could be carried
What? A swallow carrying a coconut?
I'll tell you why not ... because a swallow is about eight inches long and weighs five ounces, and you'd be lucky to find a coconut under a pound.
It's not a question of where he grips it, It's a simple matter of weight - ratios ... A five-ounce bird could not hold a one pound coconut.
It could grip it by the husk
